<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2003-04-30</DATELINE><TITLE>Gross pathology of small mammals</TITLE><BODY>A review is presented on how to perform a meaningful necropsy of the rabbit, ferret, and guinea pig. Brief descriptions of gross findings of significant diseases are provided in sufficient detail for identification in practice. Diseases are organized by organ systems affected and included based on their clinical significance, incidence, and importance in the United States.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>